In this article, President Trump discusses several topics including his upcoming visit to Dover Air Force Base, the progress made in meetings with North Korea regarding denuclearization, the positive state of trade negotiations with China, the situation in Syria and the fight against ISIS, the possibility of announcing a national emergency in relation to the border wall, and his disappointment with Mexico's handling of the migrant caravans. He also expresses his hope that Speaker Pelosi and the Democrats will recognize the effectiveness of walls and support funding for them. Additionally, he addresses the issue of federal workers affected by the government shutdown and criticizes the recent BuzzFeed article and the mainstream media's coverage, stating that they have lost credibility.